cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

This paper deals with representation and query of speech databases, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also discusses optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of annotation graphs and query language could also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
